{
  "local_port": 44008,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Good libraries in old Rajendra Nagar?",
  "response": "Rajendra Nagar, being a significant educational hub in Patna, has several good libraries that cater to the needs of students and readers. Here are some well-regarded libraries in the old Rajendra Nagar area:\n\n1. **Patna University Library**\n   - **Location**: Patna University Campus, Ashok Rajpath, Patna\n   - **Description**: While technically part of the university, it is accessible to the public and offers a vast collection of books, journals, and research materials.\n\n2. **B.N. College Library**\n   - **Location**: B.N. College Campus, Patna\n   - **Description**: Another esteemed library within an educational institution, it is known for its extensive collection and conducive reading environment.\n\n3. **Khuda Bakhsh Oriental Public Library**\n   - **Location**: Near Patna Museum, Ashok Rajpath, Patna\n   - **Description**: A historic library known for its collection of rare manuscripts and books, especially in oriental languages. It's a bit of a walk from Rajendra Nagar but worth the visit for those interested in historical texts.\n\n4. **Chanakya National Law University Library**\n   - **Location**: Nyaya Nagar, Mithapur, Patna\n   - **Description**: Specializes in legal texts and resources, it's a great resource for law students and professionals.\n\n5. **Private Libraries and Reading Rooms**\n   - **Location**: Various locations within Rajendra Nagar\n   - **Description**: There are several smaller private libraries and reading rooms that offer memberships and access to a variety of books and study materials. These might not be as well-known but can be found by asking locals or searching online.\n\nWhen visiting these libraries, it's always a good idea to check their operating hours and any specific access requirements, especially for university libraries. Happy reading!",
